Install the required libraries: pip install flask pip install cryptography 2. Create a new file called `app.py` and add the following code: ```python from flask import Flask, request, render_template from cryptography.fernet import Fernet app = Flask(__name__) @app.route('/', methods=['GET', 'POST']) def index(): if request.method == 'POST': if request.form['submit'] == 'Encrypt': key = Fernet.generate_key() f = Fernet(key) token = f.encrypt(request.form['plaintext'].encode()) return render_template('index.html', token=token.decode(), key=key.decode()) elif request.form['submit'] == 'Decrypt': f = Fernet(request.form['key'].encode()) plaintext = f.decrypt(request.form['token'].encode()) return render_template('index.html', plaintext=plaintext.decode()) return render_template('index.html') if __name__ == '__main__': app.run(debug=True) ``` 3. Create a new file called `templates/index.html` and add the following code: ```html Encryption and Decryption

Key: {{ key }}

Decryption

``` 4. Run the app: flask run 5. Visit http://127.0.0.1:5000/ in your browser. 6. Enter a plaintext message in the top form and click the "Encrypt" button. The encrypted text and key will be displayed. 7. Enter the encrypted text and key in the bottom form and click the "Decrypt" button. The decrypted plaintext will be displayed.
